Your Honor,

I, Lauren Dixon, stand before you today to plead guilty to the offense of TV licence payment evasion. I must stress that this was not intentional – I thought the bill was paid! But in reality, I had 8 months of unlicensed use.

As soon as I realized my mistake, I promptly rectified the situation by purchasing a license. This incident is an isolated event, and I have no previous criminal record.

I come before this court humbly, ready to do whatever is necessary to make amends for my mistake. I acknowledge the seriousness of this offense and the importance of adhering to the law. I assure you that I strive to be a law-abiding citizen and this situation has served as a lesson to me.

My intent is to compensate for the harm caused by my non-compliance with the TV license payment. I am committed to taking the necessary steps to rectify this, be it through financial restitution or any other means deemed appropriate by the court.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I respectfully request to be given the opportunity to make amends for my mistake. My plea of guilty demonstrates my genuine acknowledgment of my involvement in this offense. I assure you that I will continue to learn from this experience and take the necessary precautions to ensure that I adhere to the law moving forward.

Thank you.
